Sentencas: The use of conductive coating on interconnect ferritic stainless steel can reduce electrical resistivity.
Titulo: Influence of oxide scale thickness on electrical conductivity of coated AISI 430 steel for use as interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, an AISI 430 ferritic stainless steel interconnect was coated with a manganese base pack mixture by pack cementation.
Titulo: Influence of oxide scale thickness on electrical conductivity of coated AISI 430 steel for use as interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of oxide scale thickness on electrical conductivity was evaluated by applying isothermal oxidation at 750 A degrees C.
Titulo: Influence of oxide scale thickness on electrical conductivity of coated AISI 430 steel for use as interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This effect was also investigated at different temperatures (400-900 A degrees C).
Titulo: Influence of oxide scale thickness on electrical conductivity of coated AISI 430 steel for use as interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The formation of manganese spinels during annealing improved the oxidation resistance and electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Influence of oxide scale thickness on electrical conductivity of coated AISI 430 steel for use as interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results showed that the increase in isothermal oxidation time and temperature increased the oxide thickness, and this resulted in the relatively low values of electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Influence of oxide scale thickness on electrical conductivity of coated AISI 430 steel for use as interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Manganese spinels enhanced the electrical conductivity and oxidation resistance of coated substrates as compared to uncoated substrates.
Titulo: Influence of oxide scale thickness on electrical conductivity of coated AISI 430 steel for use as interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells
